<subSubSection id="17B501647C1E8703BC8141AF5813A933" pageId="19" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph id="25D06E044745A28930FC1383A7FCCF08" pageId="19" pageNumber="28">
<pageBreakToken id="574950BA3757CCCA3DBC692BA3CF6A04" pageId="19" pageNumber="28" start="start">Description</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0DD6C31AF0E666C9E2D9369DF2EFC881" pageId="19" pageNumber="28">
Since 
<bibRefCitation id="070E7D20ABE743E9FC47A2294DC92BFF" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1985.tb00875.x" author="Rudman, WB" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="22" pageNumber="31" pagination="241 - 299" refId="B19" refString="Rudman, WB, 1985. The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia, Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: Chromodoris aureomarginata, C. verrieri and C. fidelis colour groups. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 83 (3): 241 - 299, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1985.tb00875.x" title="The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia, Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: Chromodoris aureomarginata, C. verrieri and C. fidelis colour groups." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1985.tb00875.x" volume="83" year="1985">
<normalizedToken id="9F10EC9750DD0F5A4DD94DC8FE48E362" originalValue="Rudman’s">Rudman's</normalizedToken>
(1985)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="D6D7F8FA929539D94AE6E9938FA69077" author="Yonow, N" journalOrPublisher="Pensoft Publications, Sofia / Moscow" pageId="23" pageNumber="32" refId="B37" refString="Yonow, N, 2008. Red Sea Sea Slugs. Pensoft Publications, Sofia/Moscow" title="Red Sea Sea Slugs." year="2008">
<normalizedToken id="EEADD6875647D5A496F7A0471EA0305B" originalValue="Yonow’s">Yonow's</normalizedToken>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
records, 
<taxonomicName id="43D413C904112D886DB94F4D1553D1BD" baseAuthorityName="Rudman" baseAuthorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Verconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Verconia sudanica" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="19" pageNumber="28" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sudanica">
<emphasis id="B53CF1F32830591E2B0941866B5ACE48" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="28">Verconia sudanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded somewhat more frequently in the Red Sea (http://www.seaslugforum.net/showall/noumsuda, https://www.inaturalist.org/taxa/126112-Noumea-sudanica). It is described here from specimens collected in the northern Red Sea. The excellent series of photographs depict five individuals, of which three are grouped together (four specimens were collected). In the photograph of the group, the rhinophores and nine plumose but simply pinnate gills are all pure white. The edges of the rhinophore lamellae (numbering 9-11) and main axes of the gills (facing outwards) are opaque white. In photographs of a single animal, the apical one third of the rhinophore is very faintly orange, with opaque white edges to the 9-11 lamellae. All five animals have a white dorsum with pits and a narrow yellow margin, which is faintly darker orange at the edge (Plate 
<figureCitation id="CC037553BADD01CA39BC55A6DE6234FE" captionStart="Plate 10" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Plate 10. Verconia sudanica Rudman, 1985, photograph S Kahlbrock." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.770.26378.plate10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/214590" pageId="19" pageNumber="28">10</figureCitation>
). In two individuals, the pits are slightly yellow and in a third one, there are small conical papillae dotted on the surface. The foot is also white, and the tip is bordered with a yellow line; one photograph from the side shows that the margins of the foot are white.
</paragraph>
<caption id="C5059FBEB3A6E559F7C597B7FA302B2F" ID-Zenodo-Dep="1310477" doi="10.3897/zookeys.770.26378.plate10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/214590" pageId="19" pageNumber="28" start="Plate 10" startId="F16">
<paragraph id="D66173CBE43376A2A49067B9F4377FA7" pageId="19" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="DC5FCE9444F0FCCBDC35630F8695E39F" bold="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="28">Plate 10.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="0099511F6C384F762A9A48062F6652F7" baseAuthorityName="Rudman" baseAuthorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Verconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Verconia sudanica" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="19" pageNumber="28" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sudanica">
<emphasis id="A164DC024A9CD889716B0F1DE6509244" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="28">Verconia sudanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rudman, 1985, photograph S Kahlbrock.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="B8AE440A7D024A28416D37D2FA786009" pageId="19" pageNumber="28">The preserved specimens are identical, opaque cream with a thickened but slightly lighter coloured margin containing single round mantle glands that are semi-translucent. The gill pocket is large and slightly raised and in two specimens, the unipinnate gills barely protrude. The foot extends beyond the mantle slightly in all but one specimen. The foot is angular anteriorly, and the large oral tentacles are clearly visible.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D2D0B982C76D5510D951DEB682A4A23E" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="2D8A9AC9979C35272C4EB76CB86D1ABD" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">
<pageBreakToken id="1AAD004C37CC6ECF0FFE94E5C0656817" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" start="start">Remarks</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E5E9C0A9D57DB8DA152BCCF229B8440B" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">
There are no similar species in the Red Sea; only the western Pacific 
<taxonomicName id="FF5AF2E007CC5505799403C760F263B2" baseAuthorityName="Pease" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Verconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Verconia simplex" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="7A0B320133427FBFCCFCC6D1A1914523" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Verconia simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pease, 1871) is equally small, white to pale pink, with a bright orange margin; however, there are no specimen records further to the two photographs in 
<bibRefCitation id="28701B7ACA09C3B622452B11AC8D6497" author="Yonow, N" journalOrPublisher="Pensoft Publications, Sofia / Moscow" pageId="23" pageNumber="32" refId="B37" refString="Yonow, N, 2008. Red Sea Sea Slugs. Pensoft Publications, Sofia/Moscow" title="Red Sea Sea Slugs." year="2008">Yonow (2008)</bibRefCitation>
so these records remain unconfirmed. 
<taxonomicName id="8B39DC134EE6EC3E593778D450C283B6" baseAuthorityName="Pease" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Verconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Verconia simplex" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="B576500480C06AF8BD1E126E9F5AE180" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Verconia simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has bright orange tips to both the rhinophores and the gills.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B42B6FE49F12CD0DBF80AC58C97855B" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">
Some comments are necessary on the generic placement of this species. Gosliner and Johnson (2012: 6) found that 
<taxonomicName id="638E7A557B279FD4A4A9F4C1D632A965" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Noumea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D9D4E784C75EE5AB3E84B15FE297C11B" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Noumea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not monophyletic but its species were distributed in two clades (and within other genera): &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="0B12C77A904BBA3F4B6EB2F09C48B8FC" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Noumea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4FEAE92A5FD4EB5F7C3F420A9BBAF08D" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Noumea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consists of two separate clades (both pp = 1.00) that are poorly supported as a combined clade in the analysis when variable positions are included (pp = 0.61). Although this support is not sufficient, all of the species in both of these clades are currently named 
<taxonomicName id="CE1697458FE44B5395F490BA341DA0F3" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Noumea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E3FD3482691EBF7790125A04B3C2C1B" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Noumea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and will retain this name in order to maintain stability.&quot;
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E5B3EF9028ADB00BFE758BAD24B67391" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">
With this, they synonymised 
<taxonomicName id="3498C12FBD9D7313D4CCA4FD047DE276" authorityName="Pruvot-Fol" authorityYear="1931" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Verconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Verconia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="74D00CE562B459871DD2C6263BE8C145" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Verconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a monotypic genus containing 
<taxonomicName id="B7BCCA316D499A840A28A07BEA86F931" genus="V." lsidName="V. verconis" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" rank="species" species="verconis">
<emphasis id="927DDEB7AB41EE54987A81F92F0EA75F" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">V. verconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Basedow &amp; Hedley, 1905). However, they failed to recognise that 
<taxonomicName id="B142AA5B27E44F00A1E837EA12761166" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Noumea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="142A9CB3B85FCFF254F8AB19BB01D405" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Noumea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was preoccupied. WoRMS has a small note to that effect and 
<taxonomicName id="EF9968ABB887EEFD536EDF40A693ACCE" authorityName="Pruvot-Fol" authorityYear="1931" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Verconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Verconia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3442010627341C2B09832D18F587F52F" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Verconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as a synonym) should be the correct generic designation (http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=notes&amp;id=279974) despite its type species being morphologically different: &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="BE68978C963D5764D81EA145BA7A9878" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Noumea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BFA28F818B1A41A38F154474D5C6726E" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Noumea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Risbec, 1928 (
<taxonomicName id="0EC642983B3837D061A92FA1BF3B1B67" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="phylum">Mollusca</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="09D92BA8CE98F3BD63B5182C5F765194" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="class">Gastropoda</taxonomicName>
) is a junior homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="86FA8407379331D770C1F42B74FED6BA" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Noumea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="77459E38201C8021519459568DF25895" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Noumea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fauvel, 1874 (
<taxonomicName id="BA8976AE9EA7863B6BE6BBAD628F9CAA" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="phylum">Arthropoda</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="14445466248B4BECD5444CA59017919A" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
), a name in current use. 
<taxonomicName id="88A71836709FB857FC0FF2C27DAC82AC" authorityName="Pruvot-Fol" authorityYear="1931" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Verconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Verconia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7B457A54510BFE8B7925D76EC60FA068" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Verconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pruvot-Fol, 1931 was recognized as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="42420C655A75CE4F1296FDD73F854222" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Noumea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A920625B2613B9756E1946E7465DD8EE" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Noumea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Risbec by 
<bibRefCitation id="C463716B2E1E1D10BE9AFC569FBD1C2A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0033479" author="Johnson, RF" journalOrPublisher="Editions Catherine Ledru, Noumea" pageId="22" pageNumber="31" refId="B13" refString="Johnson, RF, Gosliner, TM, 2012. Traditional taxonomic groupings mask evolutionary history: A molecular phylogeny and new classification of the chromodorid nudibranchs. PLoS ONE 7(4): e33479. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0033479" title="Traditional taxonomic groupings mask evolutionary history: A molecular phylogeny and new classification of the chromodorid nudibranchs. PLoS ONE 7 (4): e 33479." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0033479" year="2012">Johnson and Gosliner (2012)</bibRefCitation>
and is here used for species of the chromodoridid group previously known as 
<taxonomicName id="1D33CF1F9088024D723EEBC3CAE39054" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Noumea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="669AA0A8765B8FF83ED438F358B50217" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Noumea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.&quot;
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6928E75E82A00103AA4E1CBD72596B0D" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">
Examination of 
<bibRefCitation id="ECC9A2187CD40F074BE164401E0140AE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1984.tb01174.x" author="Rudman, WB" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="22" pageNumber="31" pagination="115 - 273" refId="B18" refString="Rudman, WB, 1984. The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia, Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: a review of the genera. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 81: 115 - 273, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1984.tb01174.x" title="The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia, Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: a review of the genera." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1984.tb01174.x" volume="81" year="1984">
<normalizedToken id="D374D49D6432A5004D6D40F44D131651" originalValue="Rudman’s">Rudman's</normalizedToken>
(1984)
</bibRefCitation>
review of the chromodorid genera and his descriptions of species of 
<taxonomicName id="1D3C95D2BB847A79F1C9508A6773232A" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Noumea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="42731E4583607FFA770585064428D6EC" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Noumea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="303EE6FE253154EF1E660560E4A95B4B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01810.x" author="Rudman, WB" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal Linnean Society" pageId="22" pageNumber="31" pagination="101 - 184" refId="B20" refString="Rudman, WB, 1986a. The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia, Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: the genus Glossodoris Ehrenberg (= Casella Hancock and A. Adams). Zoological Journal Linnean Society 86 (2): 101 - 184, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01810.x" title="The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia, Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: the genus Glossodoris Ehrenberg (= Casella Hancock and A. Adams)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01810.x" volume="86" year="1986 a">Rudman 1986a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F435B76BA110EFD24902775700FB9543" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01814.x" author="Rudman, WB" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="22" pageNumber="31" pagination="309 - 353" refId="B21" refString="Rudman, WB, 1986b. The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia: Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: Noumea purpurea and Chromodoris decora colour groups. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 86 (4): 309 - 353, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01814.x" title="The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia: Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: Noumea purpurea and Chromodoris decora colour groups." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01814.x" volume="86" year="1986 b">b</bibRefCitation>
) show that these two genera are in fact similar, but because the external morphology of 
<taxonomicName id="EDE8280C5E8F875AE117660E088FA06C" baseAuthorityName="Basedow &amp; Hedley" baseAuthorityYear="1905" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Verconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Verconia verconis" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="verconis">
<emphasis id="B48EB1D94DA348A70FBF3B6AF6374788" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Verconia verconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is so distinctive, it has historically been considered in its own genus. The radular formulae and teeth shapes are very similar, as are some morphological characters (although these are also similar to other chromodorid genera). The reproductive systems vary a little within the group described as 
<taxonomicName id="39B032B6927DFA9058FBDB3D10FEA869" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Noumea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BDD761D09755211AB27ECD70505A9597" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Noumea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="9B8193D41F3A8839B3ED8BF565175E97" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1984.tb01174.x" author="Rudman, WB" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="22" pageNumber="31" pagination="115 - 273" refId="B18" refString="Rudman, WB, 1984. The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia, Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: a review of the genera. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 81: 115 - 273, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1984.tb01174.x" title="The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia, Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: a review of the genera." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1984.tb01174.x" volume="81" year="1984">Rudman (1984</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9782EB371D016AEEC25A05234AED9C15" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01810.x" author="Rudman, WB" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal Linnean Society" pageId="22" pageNumber="31" pagination="101 - 184" refId="B20" refString="Rudman, WB, 1986a. The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia, Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: the genus Glossodoris Ehrenberg (= Casella Hancock and A. Adams). Zoological Journal Linnean Society 86 (2): 101 - 184, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01810.x" title="The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia, Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: the genus Glossodoris Ehrenberg (= Casella Hancock and A. Adams)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01810.x" volume="86" year="1986 a">1986a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="2AD406B647958F1647CF081A8FFD165B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01814.x" author="Rudman, WB" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="22" pageNumber="31" pagination="309 - 353" refId="B21" refString="Rudman, WB, 1986b. The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia: Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: Noumea purpurea and Chromodoris decora colour groups. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 86 (4): 309 - 353, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01814.x" title="The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia: Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: Noumea purpurea and Chromodoris decora colour groups." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01814.x" volume="86" year="1986 b">b</bibRefCitation>
although some species belonging to a second clade have been re-assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="5B761BECAF4EF40FBFE80B5E1CBE5533" authorityName="Rudman" authorityYear="1987" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Diversidoris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diversidoris" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71426D5F90E72CEC1496C50941B9CD83" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Diversidoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and in some cases are more similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="41D3C231A2F995324564584D32B184EC" genus="V." lsidName="V. verconis" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" rank="species" species="verconis">
<emphasis id="DB9DB1EF936641B87C51879BE4DB75D9" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">V. verconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see also 
<bibRefCitation id="C4ED4644E49F18BE2C4136984D489EAD" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01814.x" author="Rudman, WB" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="22" pageNumber="31" pagination="309 - 353" refId="B21" refString="Rudman, WB, 1986b. The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia: Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: Noumea purpurea and Chromodoris decora colour groups. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 86 (4): 309 - 353, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01814.x" title="The Chromodorididae (Opisthobranchia: Mollusca) of the Indo-West Pacific: Noumea purpurea and Chromodoris decora colour groups." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1986.tb01814.x" volume="86" year="1986 b">Rudman 1986b</bibRefCitation>
: 402). As it is very unlikely that the specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="97FDF3CD133C7EF7BAA498658136F560" genus="V." lsidName="V. verconis" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" rank="species" species="verconis">
<emphasis id="FB000C4F3748CB744EB359248F3E9DBA" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">V. verconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
used in the molecular analysis by 
<bibRefCitation id="22F6E901F17767F48447BFBBCE56CC8E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0033479" author="Johnson, RF" journalOrPublisher="Editions Catherine Ledru, Noumea" pageId="22" pageNumber="31" refId="B13" refString="Johnson, RF, Gosliner, TM, 2012. Traditional taxonomic groupings mask evolutionary history: A molecular phylogeny and new classification of the chromodorid nudibranchs. PLoS ONE 7(4): e33479. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0033479" title="Traditional taxonomic groupings mask evolutionary history: A molecular phylogeny and new classification of the chromodorid nudibranchs. PLoS ONE 7 (4): e 33479." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0033479" year="2012">Johnson and Gosliner (2012)</bibRefCitation>
were misidentified, the synonymy must be accepted, but it is unfortunate that these authors did not examine the literature and, as a result, the species they assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="26B44106E103E883D1E9CB0456ACE571" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Noumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Noumea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="695B5C1C9E409BFD454446223181317B" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Noumea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must now be reassigned to 
<taxonomicName id="40E4928A669BFAF0942AA0A776E5D0BD" authorityName="Pruvot-Fol" authorityYear="1931" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Verconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Verconia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="20" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4076335DF239D32899E33E556B878197" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="29">Verconia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
